---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Our Policies | Fusion Victoria - Evidence-Based Solutions"
  description="50,000 public homes. Melton Line by 2029. Wage theft criminalised. 100% renewables by 2030. Evidence-based policies with full costings."
>
  <Header />
  
  <Hero 
    title="Our Policies"
    subtitle="Evidence-based solutions. Full costings. Real results."
  />

  <!-- POLICY OVERVIEW -->
  <section class="bg-white py-16 px-8">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="bg-magenta-light border-l-4 border-magenta p-8 rounded mb-12">
        <p class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">The major parties waste billions on poorly planned projects while telling you there's "no money" for housing, healthcare, or transport.</p>
        <p class="text-3xl font-black text-magenta">We're taking it back.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 mb-12">
        {['Housing', 'Workers\' Rights', 'Transport', 'Healthcare', 'Climate', 'Infrastructure', 'Fiscal Responsibility'].map(policy => (
          <a href={`#${policy.toLowerCase().replace(/[']/g, '').replace(/\s+/g, '-')}`} class="bg-lavender hover:bg-magenta-solid text-white font-bold py-3 px-4 rounded text-center transition-all hover:scale-105">
            {policy}
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HOUSING -->
  <section id="housing" class="bg-light-grey py-20 px-8">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-magenta mb-8">üè† Housing: End The Scam</h2>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-8 rounded">
          <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">The Problem:</h4>
          <p class="text-lg">You're paying 60% of your income in rent while property investors claim <strong>$3.2 billion/year in tax breaks</strong>. 54,000 Victorian families wait for public housing. The government promises 80,000 homes over ten years - barely enough to keep up with demand growth.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-mint-light border-l-4 border-mint p-8 rounded">
          <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-magenta mb-4">Our Solution:</h4>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Build 50,000 new public homes over 4 years</strong> (12,500/year)</li>
            <li><strong>Buy one floor of every new tower over 10 stories</strong> for public housing - mixed communities, not ghettos</li>
            <li><strong>Mandate 15% of all new developments</strong> go to public/affordable housing</li>
            <li><strong>Ban no-grounds evictions</strong> - if you're paying rent on time, you have security</li>
            <li><strong>Cap rent increases at CPI + 2% maximum</strong>, once per year</li>
            <li><strong>Rental Commissioner</strong> with real enforcement powers</li>
            <li><strong>Portable rental bonds</strong></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md mb-8">
        <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-magenta mb-4">How We Pay For It:</h4>
        <div class="space-y-2 mb-4">
          <p class="text-lg">50,000 homes at $500k = <strong>$25 billion borrowed</strong></p>
          <p class="text-lg">Rental return at 25% market rent: <strong>$625 million/year</strong></p>
          <p class="text-lg">Bond interest at 4%: <strong>$1 billion/year</strong></p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-magenta">Real net cost: <strong>~$100 million/year</strong></p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-magenta">Return on investment: <strong>4% direct, 8% with externalities</strong></p>
        </div>
        <p class="text-xl font-semibold italic">This isn't spending. It's investing in assets that generate returns while housing people.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-magenta-solid text-white p-6 rounded-lg">
        <strong class="text-xl">First 100 Days:</strong> Establish Victorian Public Housing Authority. Begin procurement for first 5,000 homes. Introduce rental protection legislation.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WORKERS' RIGHTS -->
  <section id="workers-rights" class="bg-white py-20 px-8">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-magenta mb-8">‚öñÔ∏è Workers' Rights: Stop The Theft</h2>
      
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-magenta mb-6">Criminalise Wage Theft</h3>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-8 rounded">
            <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">The Problem:</h4>
            <p class="text-lg">Victorian workers lose <strong>$1.35 billion/year to wage theft</strong>. Current penalties cost less than just paying people properly.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-mint-light border-l-4 border-mint p-8 rounded">
            <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-magenta mb-4">Our Solution:</h4>
            <ul class="space-y-2">
              <li><strong>Make deliberate wage theft a criminal offence</strong> with jail time for directors</li>
              <li><strong>Triple the Wage Inspectorate budget</strong> to $60 million/year</li>
              <li><strong>Reverse the burden of proof</strong> - employers must prove they paid correctly</li>
              <li><strong>Personal liability for directors</strong></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-magenta mb-6">Fix The Gig Economy</h3>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-8 rounded">
            <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">The Problem:</h4>
            <p class="text-lg">30% of Victorian workers are casual/gig. Platforms classify you as "contractor" to avoid minimum wage, super, leave.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-mint-light border-l-4 border-mint p-8 rounded">
            <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-magenta mb-4">Our Solution:</h4>
            <ul class="space-y-2">
              <li><strong>Presume all gig workers are employees</strong> unless platform proves otherwise</li>
              <li><strong>Minimum pay rates</strong> equivalent to award wages</li>
              <li><strong>Portable long service leave</strong> across gig economy</li>
              <li><strong>Mandatory workers compensation</strong> coverage</li>
              <li><strong>Victorian Gig Economy Ombudsman</strong> with enforcement powers</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-8 rounded">
        <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-700 mb-4">Universal Basic Income</h4>
        <p class="text-lg mb-2"><strong>Federal Policy - We'll Pressure Canberra</strong></p>
        <p class="text-lg mb-2"><strong>UBI at Henderson Poverty Line (~$30,000/year)</strong>. No mutual obligations. No poverty trap. Foundation for freedom.</p>
        <p class="text-lg">We'll run pilot programs in Victoria, publish evidence, and pressure federal government relentlessly.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TRANSPORT -->
  <section id="transport" class="bg-light-grey py-20 px-8">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-magenta mb-8">üöÇ Transport: Fix The Failures</h2>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-8 rounded">
          <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">The Problem:</h4>
          <p class="text-lg">Melton Line promised since 2009 - <strong>$750 million wasted in interest</strong>. 30,000 homes approved in Clyde with one overwhelmed train line. You're losing two hours a day to their failures.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-mint-light border-l-4 border-mint p-8 rounded">
          <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-magenta mb-4">Our Solution:</h4>
          <p class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Targeted fixes for growth corridors:</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border-2 border-mint hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <h5 class="text-xl font-bold text-magenta mb-3">Melton Line</h5>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Electrify and duplicate within 4 years</strong></li>
            <li>Triple frequency to match metro lines</li>
            <li>Cost: ~$2 billion</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border-2 border-mint hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <h5 class="text-xl font-bold text-magenta mb-3">Clyde/Officer/Pakenham</h5>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Build the second track now</strong></li>
            <li>Express services during peak</li>
            <li>Cost: ~$1.5 billion</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border-2 border-mint hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <h5 class="text-xl font-bold text-magenta mb-3">Wyndham Vale/Tarneit</h5>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li>Quadruple parking at stations</li>
            <li>15-minute bus frequencies</li>
            <li>Cost: ~$300 million parking + $50M/year buses</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border-2 border-mint hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <h5 class="text-xl font-bold text-magenta mb-3">Sunbury</h5>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li>Electrify to Sunbury (currently ends at Watergardens)</li>
            <li>20-minute frequency all day</li>
            <li>Cost: ~$800 million</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md mb-8">
        <h5 class="text-2xl font-bold text-magenta mb-4">Overall System</h5>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg">
          <li><strong>Free trams in all CBD zones</strong></li>
          <li><strong>20-minute minimum frequency</strong> on all lines, all day</li>
          <li><strong>Integrated fares:</strong> $10/day cap</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-magenta-solid text-white p-8 rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">High-Speed Rail</h3>
        <h5 class="text-xl font-bold text-mint mb-3">Stage 1: Melbourne-Geelong-Ballarat (200km/h)</h5>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg">
          <li>45 minutes Melbourne-Geelong</li>
          <li>60 minutes Melbourne-Ballarat</li>
          <li>Opens up 200,000+ affordable homes</li>
          <li>Cost: ~$10 billion over 6 years</li>
          <li>50% federal, 25% value capture, 25% bonds</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HEALTHCARE -->
  <section id="healthcare" class="bg-white py-20 px-8">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-magenta mb-8">üè• Healthcare: End The Two-Tier Scam</h2>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-8 rounded">
          <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">The Problem:</h4>
          <p class="text-lg">You wait six months for surgery. <strong>$1.5 billion in tax revenue subsidises private hospitals</strong> through exemptions. They poach staff and let wealthy people jump the queue.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-mint-light border-l-4 border-mint p-8 rounded">
          <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-magenta mb-4">Our Solution:</h4>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Increase public hospital funding by 30%</strong> over 4 years ($3B/year by year 4)</li>
            <li><strong>Build 4 new public hospitals</strong> in growth corridors: Clyde, Melton, Wyndham, North Melbourne (~$8B over 6 years)</li>
            <li><strong>End private hospital tax exemptions</strong> unless they treat public patients at public rates (+$400M/year)</li>
            <li><strong>Triple elective surgery capacity</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Fix ambulance ramping</strong> with nurse-led streaming</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-8 rounded mb-8">
        <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-700 mb-2">Federal Fight:</h4>
        <p class="text-lg">We can't expand Medicare to dental/mental health alone - that's federal. But we'll pressure federal MPs relentlessly and build the public case.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-magenta-solid text-white p-6 rounded-lg">
        <strong class="text-xl">First 100 Days:</strong> Inject $750 million immediately to public hospitals. Begin procurement for Clyde and Melton hospitals. End private hospital tax exemptions.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CLIMATE -->
  <section id="climate" class="bg-light-grey py-20 px-8">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-magenta mb-8">üåç Climate: Renewable Energy That Pays For Itself</h2>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-8 rounded">
          <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">The Problem:</h4>
          <p class="text-lg">Victoria still generates 30% from coal. Government subsidises fossil fuels while you pay high energy bills. Major parties take fossil fuel donations.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-mint-light border-l-4 border-mint p-8 rounded">
          <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-magenta mb-4">Our Solution:</h4>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li><strong>100% renewable electricity by 2030</strong> (not 2035)</li>
            <li><strong>End all fossil fuel subsidies</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Build 2GW state-owned renewable energy</strong> (solar/wind/battery)</li>
            <li><strong>Fast-track renewable energy zones</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Abolish stamp duty on EVs under $60k</strong>, increase on petrol cars over $60k</li>
            <li><strong>EV fast chargers:</strong> One every 5km on highways</li>
            <li><strong>Green Jobs Transition Authority</strong> for Latrobe Valley workers</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md">
        <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-magenta mb-4">State-Owned Renewables Are Smart Investment:</h4>
        <div class="space-y-2 mb-4">
          <p class="text-lg">2GW renewable + battery: <strong>$3 billion capital</strong></p>
          <p class="text-lg">Revenue from energy sales: <strong>$400 million/year</strong></p>
          <p class="text-lg">Bond interest: <strong>$120 million/year</strong></p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-magenta">Net return: <strong>$280 million/year</strong></p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-magenta">Pays itself off in 11 years, then pure profit</p>
        </div>
        <p class="text-xl font-semibold italic">This is buying assets that generate revenue while cutting emissions.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- INFRASTRUCTURE -->
  <section id="infrastructure" class="bg-white py-20 px-8">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-magenta mb-8">üèóÔ∏è Infrastructure: Stop The Waste</h2>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-8 rounded">
          <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">The Problem:</h4>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg">
            <li>West Gate Tunnel: $5.5B ‚Üí $15B (<strong>$9.5B wasted</strong>)</li>
            <li>Melton Line: 16 years delayed (<strong>$750M wasted</strong>)</li>
            <li>Auditor-General: <strong>30% average cost overruns</strong></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-mint-light border-l-4 border-mint p-8 rounded">
          <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-magenta mb-4">Our Solution:</h4>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Give Infrastructure Victoria binding authority</strong> on all projects over $100M</li>
            <li><strong>No development approvals over 1,000 dwellings</strong> without IV certification that infrastructure will be built within 2 years</li>
            <li><strong>Transparent 30-year pipeline</strong> with quarterly updates</li>
            <li><strong>Community consultation with teeth</strong></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md border-2 border-mint">
        <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-magenta mb-4">Savings:</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg">
          <li>Reduce overruns from 30% to 10%: <strong>$1.5 billion/year</strong></li>
          <li>Cancel marginal projects: <strong>$500 million/year</strong></li>
          <li class="text-2xl font-bold text-magenta pt-4 border-t-2 border-gray-200"><strong>Total: $2 billion/year to redirect</strong> to housing, hospitals, transport</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FISCAL RESPONSIBILITY -->
  <section id="fiscal-responsibility" class="bg-light-grey py-20 px-8">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-magenta mb-8">üí∞ Fiscal Responsibility: Smart Investment Beats Dumb Waste</h2>
      
      <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-8 rounded mb-8">
        <p class="text-xl mb-2"><strong>Their Attack:</strong> "Fusion will blow out debt!"</p>
        <p class="text-xl"><strong>The Truth:</strong> Victoria's debt is already $177B and climbing because they waste money on an industrial scale.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-magenta mb-8 text-center">Our Three-Point Plan:</h3>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-12">
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md">
          <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-magenta mb-4">1. Stop Waste ($2.8B/year)</h4>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li>Cut overruns 30%‚Üí10%: <strong>$1.5B/year</strong></li>
            <li>Cancel marginal projects: <strong>$500M/year</strong></li>
            <li>Procurement reform: <strong>$400M/year</strong></li>
            <li>Cut consultancy waste: <strong>$400M/year</strong></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md">
          <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-magenta mb-4">2. Grow Revenue ($2B/year)</h4>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li>Land Value Tax: <strong>+$800M/year</strong></li>
            <li>End hospital exemptions: <strong>+$400M/year</strong></li>
            <li>Close tax gap: <strong>+$500M/year</strong></li>
            <li>Value capture: <strong>+$300M/year</strong></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md">
          <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-magenta mb-4">3. Smart Investment</h4>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li>Public housing: 4-8% returns</li>
            <li>Renewables: $280M/year net</li>
            <li>Transport: enables growth</li>
            <li>All via IV cost-benefit analysis</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg mb-8">
        <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-magenta mb-6 text-center">The Results:</h4>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full">
            <thead class="bg-magenta-solid text-white">
              <tr>
                <th class="p-4 text-left">Metric</th>
                <th class="p-4 text-left">Labor's Path</th>
                <th class="p-4 text-left">Fusion's Path</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b">
                <td class="p-4 font-semibold">2030 Debt</td>
                <td class="p-4">$250B (32% GSP)</td>
                <td class="p-4 font-bold text-mint">$210B (25% GSP)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
                <td class="p-4 font-semibold">Public Housing</td>
                <td class="p-4">80k over 10yr</td>
                <td class="p-4 font-bold text-mint">50k over 4yr</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b">
                <td class="p-4 font-semibold">Melton Line</td>
                <td class="p-4">"Planned"</td>
                <td class="p-4 font-bold text-mint">Built by 2029</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="p-4 font-semibold">Annual Waste</td>
                <td class="p-4">$2.8B+</td>
                <td class="p-4 font-bold text-mint">&lt;$1B</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-center text-xl font-bold">Full costings at <a href="https://fusionparty.org.au/costings" class="text-magenta underline hover:text-mint">fusionparty.org.au/costings</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-magenta-gradient text-white py-20 px-8 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black mb-6">These Policies Can Win</h2>
      <p class="text-xl mb-10">But only if we build a movement that can't be ignored. Join us.</p>
      
      <div class="cta-buttons">
        <a href="/get-involved" class="btn btn-primary">Get Involved</a>
        <a href="/manifesto" class="btn btn-secondary">Read Full Manifesto</a>
        <a href="https://fusionparty.org.au/costings" class="btn btn-secondary">View Costings</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
